You already linked your JavaScript file correctly:

```html
<script src="main.js" defer></script>
```

Now here’s the full structure and how to control everything from `main.js`.

# Basic HTML Structure

```html
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <title>My Website</title>

    <!-- CSS File -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

    <!-- JS File -->
    <script src="main.js" defer></script>
</head>

<body>

    <h1 id="heading">Hello</h1>

    <p class="text">Welcome to my website</p>

</body>
</html>
```

---

# Folder Structure

```text
project/
│
├── index.html
├── style.css
└── main.js
```

---

# 1. Change `<title>` using JavaScript

Inside `main.js`

```js
document.title = "New Website Title";
```

---

# 2. Add Elements to `<body>`

```js
const para = document.createElement("p");

para.textContent = "This paragraph was added by JavaScript";

document.body.appendChild(para);
```

---

# 3. Add HTML Inside Body

```js
document.body.innerHTML += `
    <div>
        <h2>New Section</h2>
        <p>Added from JS</p>
    </div>
`;
```

---

# 4. Access and Change Existing Elements

HTML:

```html
<h1 id="heading">Hello</h1>
```

JS:

```js
const heading = document.getElementById("heading");

heading.textContent = "Changed by JavaScript";
```

---

# 5. Add CSS File Dynamically

```js
const css = document.createElement("link");

css.rel = "stylesheet";
css.href = "style.css";

document.head.appendChild(css);
```

---

# 6. Add CSS Directly from JS

```js
document.body.style.backgroundColor = "black";
document.body.style.color = "white";
```

---

# 7. Add New JS File Dynamically

```js
const script = document.createElement("script");

script.src = "extra.js";

document.body.appendChild(script);
```

---

# 8. Add Anything Inside `<head>`

```js
const meta = document.createElement("meta");

meta.name = "description";
meta.content = "My website description";

document.head.appendChild(meta);
```

---

# 9. Full Example (`main.js`)

```js
// Change title
document.title = "JavaScript Website";

// Create heading
const h1 = document.createElement("h1");
h1.textContent = "Created from JavaScript";

// Add style
h1.style.color = "blue";

// Add to body
document.body.appendChild(h1);

// Create paragraph
const p = document.createElement("p");
p.textContent = "This paragraph was also created using JS.";

document.body.appendChild(p);
```

---

# Important Concepts

| Part              | Meaning                  |
| ----------------- | ------------------------ |
| `document.head`   | Controls `<head>`        |
| `document.body`   | Controls `<body>`        |
| `createElement()` | Creates new HTML element |
| `appendChild()`   | Adds element to page     |
| `textContent`     | Changes text             |
| `innerHTML`       | Adds HTML                |
| `style`           | Adds CSS                 |

---

# Best Practice

Usually:

* HTML → structure
* CSS → design
* JS → functionality

Example:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
<script src="main.js" defer></script>
```

This is the standard method used in real websites.





















